The paper discusses a knowledge engine for robots to carry out tasks, which involves dealing with multiple data modalities including symbols, natural language, haptic senses, robot trajectories, and visual features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses technical aspects such as modeling correctness of knowledge, inferring latent information, and formulating different robotic tasks as queries to the knowledge engine, which are relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions perception and planning, which are key areas in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), respectively.
